### Backend: Manejo de Errores

```typescript
// OpciÃģn 1: Usar createRouteHandler (recomendado)
router.get('/items', createRouteHandler(async (req) => {
  return await getItems(); // Errores se manejan automÃĄticamente
}));

// OpciÃģn 2: Manejo manual (casos especiales)
import { createErrorResponse, getStatusCodeFromError } from '../utils/error-response';

try {
  // ... lÃģgica
} catch (error) {
  const statusCode = getStatusCodeFromError(error);
  return res.status(statusCode).json(
    createErrorResponse({
      error,
      requestId: req.requestId,
      userMessage: 'Failed to process request',
    })
  );
}
```

### Frontend: Manejo de Errores

```typescript
